When you are done, your chenille stem should be half its length and have only two bumps. Pinch the folded parts between your forefinger and thumb to create nice, sharp points. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/3c/Make-a-Poinsettia-Garland-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Poinsettia-Garland-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/3/3c/Make-a-Poinsettia-Garland-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/aid8170747-v4-728px-Make-a-Poinsettia-Garland-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Twist the loose ends around the center of the stem. This will hold your petals together. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/71/Make-a-Poinsettia-Garland-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Poinsettia-Garland-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/7/71/Make-a-Poinsettia-Garland-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/aid8170747-v4-728px-Make-a-Poinsettia-Garland-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Run your craft blade along the edge of a metal ruler to make your cuts nice and straight; you can also use a paper cutter instead. Use ivory scrapbooking paper to make white poinsettias. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/25/Make-a-Poinsettia-Garland-Step-10Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Poinsettia-Garland-Step-10Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/2/25/Make-a-Poinsettia-Garland-Step-10Bullet1.jpg/aid8170747-v4-728px-Make-a-Poinsettia-Garland-Step-10Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
